==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heating
<hw>Heat"ing</hw> <pr>(h⟦emac⟧t"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>That
heats or imparts heat; promoting warmth or heat; exciting action;
stimulating; <as>as, <ex>heating</ex> medicines or
applications</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Heating surface</b></col> <fld>(Steam Boilers)</fld>,
<cd>the aggregate surface exposed to fire or to the heated products of
combustion, esp. of all the plates or sheets that are exposed to water
on their opposite surfaces; -- called also <altname>fire
surface</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heatingly</ent>⟦br⟧
